\f2\b \cf0 3. Coding for Growl\
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\fi720\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0 \cf0 All communication with Growl by client applications takes place through 
\f3\fs20 NSDistributedObjectCenter
\f1\fs24 , using keys and notifications defined in 
\f3\fs20 GrowlDefines.h
\f1\fs24 . \
Note that there is (currently) no Growl -> Client communication. This should change shortly.\
When a Growl-enabled application launches, it should post a notification named 
\f3\fs20 GROWL_APP_REGISTRATION
\f1\fs24 , with a userInfo dictionary with the following key => value pairs:\
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\fi720\ql\qnatural

\f3\fs20 \cf0 GROWL_APP_NAME		=>	
\f1\fs24 The name of the application registering itself\
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li5040\fi-4320\ql\qnatural

\f3\fs20 \cf0 GROWL_NOTIFICATIONS_ALL	=>	
\f1\fs24 An 
\f3\fs20 NSArray *
\f1\fs24  of the names of all the notifications the application will send out.\

\f3\fs20 GROWL_NOTIFICATIONS_DEFAULT	=>	
\f1\fs24 An 
\f3\fs20 NSArray *
\f1\fs24  of the subset of the notifications specified in 
\f3\fs20 GROWL_NOTIFICATIONS_ALL 
\f1\fs24 that should be enabled to be displayed by default.\
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\fi720\ql\qnatural
\cf0 When an application registers with Growl, Growl will retrieve the icon for the application named in the registration request, and cache it to use as a default icon later.\
Once an application has registered with Growl, it can proceed to send out event notifications to Growl, to be (possibly, dependent on preferences) displayed. This event should be sent in the form of a notification through 
\f3\fs20 NSDistributedObjectCenter
\f1\fs24 . The name of the notification should be one of the names the application supplied in the 
\f3\fs20 GROWL_NOTIFICATIONS_ALL 
\f1\fs24 list it registered with, and its userInfo dictionary should contain the following key => value pairs:\
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li5040\fi-4320\ql\qnatural

\f3\fs20 \cf0 GROWL_APP_NAME		=>	
\f1\fs24 The name of the application sending the notification; This should be the same name used in registering the app.\
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li5040\fi-4320\ql\qnatural

\f3\fs20 \cf0 \CocoaLigature0 GROWL_NOTIFICATION_TITLE =>	
\f1\fs24 The title of the notification.\

\f3\fs20 GROWL_NOTIFICATION_DESCRIPTION => 
\f1\fs24 The description for the notification.\

\f3\fs20 GROWL_NOTIFICATION_ICON	=>	
\f1\fs24 Optionally (a default will be found as specified above if this is nil or not present), an 
\f3\fs20 NSData *
\f1\fs24  containing a TIFF representation of an icon associated with the notification.\
\pard\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\fi720\ql\qnatural
\cf0 That's all there is to it. \
